Package com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue

Interface QueueContract

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.microsoft.windowsazure.core.FilterableService<QueueContract>, com.microsoft.windowsazure.core.pipeline.jersey.JerseyFilterableService<QueueContract>

    public interface QueueContract
extends com.microsoft.windowsazure.core.pipeline.jersey.JerseyFilterableService<QueueContract>
    Defines the methods available on the Windows Azure storage queue service. Construct an object instance implementing QueueContract with one of the static create methods on QueueService. These methods associate a Configuration with the implementation, so the methods on the instance of QueueContract all work with a particular storage account.

      • listMessages

        ListMessagesResult listMessages​(java.lang.String queue)
                         throws com.microsoft.windowsazure.exception.ServiceException
        Retrieves the first message from head of the named queue in the storage account. This marks the message as invisible for the default visibility timeout period. When message processing is complete, the message must be deleted with a call to deleteMessage. If message processing will take longer than the visibility timeout period, use the updateMessage method to extend the visibility timeout. The message will become visible in the queue again when the timeout completes if it is not deleted.

        To get a list of multiple messages from the head of the queue, call the listMessages(String, ListMessagesOptions) method with options set specifying the number of messages to return.

        Parameters:
        queue - A String containing the name of the queue to get the message from.
        Returns:
        A ListMessagesResult reference to the message result returned.
        Throws:
        com.microsoft.windowsazure.exception.ServiceException - if an error occurs in the storage service.

      • listMessages

        ListMessagesResult listMessages​(java.lang.String queue,
                                ListMessagesOptions options)
                         throws com.microsoft.windowsazure.exception.ServiceException
        Retrieves up to 32 messages from the head of the named queue in the storage account, using the specified options. Use the options parameter to specify the server timeout for the operation, the number of messages to retrieve, and the visibility timeout to set on the retrieved messages. When message processing is complete, each message must be deleted with a call to deleteMessage. If message processing takes longer than the default timeout period, use the updateMessage method to extend the visibility timeout. Each message will become visible in the queue again when the timeout completes if it is not deleted.
        Parameters:
        queue - A String containing the name of the queue to get the messages from.
        options - A ListMessagesOptions instance containing options for the request.
        Returns:
        A ListMessagesResult reference to the message result returned.
        Throws:
        com.microsoft.windowsazure.exception.ServiceException - if an error occurs in the storage service.
